    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>Band 8: High sensitivity observations of the [CI]3P1-3P0 line in NGC6240</prj:name>
        <prj:note>Our aim is obtain an high sensitivity map of the [CI]3P1-3P0 emission line in the local LIRG NGC6240. We want to probe the capability of this fine structure transition to trace the bulk of the molecular gas and compare it to the more commonly used CO(1-0) (and 13CO(1-0)). Moreover, we want to detect the faint and broad component of the [CI] line, tracing the massive molecular outflow discovered in this source through CO, and test [CI] as an H_2 outflow tracer, which would have important applications to the study of high redshift (z&gt;2) galaxies, for which low-J CO emission lines are not observable with ALMA.</prj:note>
